8.  The  research  analyst  (6  person-months,  intermittent)  will  have  a  background  in 
conducting socioeconomic research and performing conference secretariat functions. He or she 
will be based in Manila and will: 

(i)  collect,  review,  and  synthesize  available  and  related  articles,  databases, 
documents, and publications on climate change and migration and the social 
dimensions of climate change; 
(ii)  support the preparation of briefs, presentations, write-ups for the TA; 
(iii)  assist  in  coordinatingbetween  the  consultants  and  ADB  staff,  DMCs,  and 
development partners; 
(iv)  provide logistical and administrative support to workshops, knowledge exchange, 
and the preparation of dialogues and publications; and 
(v)  perform other tasks related to the TA.
